Wander_Wallet_NS6: Tour Budget Visualizer
WanderWallet is a full-stack client-server application designed to provide travelers with an instant, visual breakdown of their trip expenses. It bridges the gap between complex logistical planning and user-friendly design by combining real-time data processing with interactive visualizations.
ğŸš€ Features
 * Request-Response Architecture: Uses a Python Flask backend to handle logic and an HTML/JS frontend for the user interface.
 * Real-time Calculations: Processes distance, number of members, and tour duration against "pretrained" values for fuel efficiency and daily costs.
 * Dynamic Visualizations: Generates five interactive chart types (Bar, Pie, Doughnut, Polar Area, and Line) using Chart.js to help users understand their spending weight.
 * Modern Glassmorphism UI: Features a sleek, semi-transparent frosted glass design with vibrant linear gradients and glowing interactive elements.
 * Intro Animations: Professional scale-and-blur entrance animations for a polished first impression.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

 * Backend: Python (Flask)
 * Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Custom Animations), JavaScript (ES6+)
 * Data Visualization: Chart.js
 * Communication: Asynchronous JSON data exchange via Fetch API

ğŸ“ Math Logic

The application uses specific real-world variables stored securely on the server:
 * Fuel Expense: Calculated as \frac{Distance}{Efficiency} \times Fuel Price.
 * Accommodation: Automatically calculates costs based on nights stayed (e.g., â‚¹0 for same-day returns).
 * Rates: * Bike: 30 km/liter at â‚¹109.52/liter.
   * Car: 11 km/liter at â‚¹101.32/liter.
   * Daily Costs: â‚¹270 for food and â‚¹700 for accommodation per person.
